        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"In this part we learn:\n\n1. Adjective qualifying a definite noun, e.g."}]},
        {"mode":"text","d":"ltr", "words":[{"w":"where is the new teacher?"}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"أَيْنَ","e":"where"},{"w":"الْمُدَرِّسُ","e":"teacher","sp":[0,3]},{"w":"الْجَدِيدُ؟","e":"new","sp":[0,3]}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"2. Relative pronoun الَّذِي . If it refers to a human being it is to be translated \"who\", and if it refers to an animal or a thing \"which\", e.g."}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"الرَّجُلُ  الَّذِي  خَرَجَ  مِنَ  الْمَسْجِدِ  الآنَ  تَاجِرٌ  شَهِيرٌ."}]},
        {"mode":"text","d":"ltr", "words":[{"w":"The man who went out of the mosque just now is a famous merchant."}]},
        {"mode":"text", "words":[{"w":"البَيْتُ  الَّذِي  أَمَامَ  الْمَسْجِدِ  لِلإِمَمِ."}]},
        {"mode":"text","d":"ltr", "words":[{"w":"The house which is in front of the mosque belongs to the imam."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"3. Note that when لِ is used with a noun having اَلْ, the alif of اَلْ is omitted: "}]},
        {"mode":"vocab", "words":[{"w":"الإِمَامُ","e":""},{"w":"لِلإِمَامِ","e":""},{"w":"الْمُدَرِّسُ","e":""},{"w":"لِلْمُدَرِّسِ","e":""}]},
        {"d":"ltr","words":[{"w":"4. عِنْدَ \"with\". The noun follows it has <<-i>> ending e.g. "}]},
        {"mode":"text","words":[{"w":"الْمُدَرِّسُ  عِنْدَ  الْمُدِيرُ."}]},
        {"d":"ltr","mode":"text","words":[{"w":"The teacher is with the headmaster."}]},
